<item>
            <title>[JDK-8336342] Fix known X11 library locations in sysroot</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8336342</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>In &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8257913&quot; title=&quot;Add more known library locations to simplify Linux cross-compilation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8257913&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8257913&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we added the search paths for X11 libraries, but they point explicitly to `libX11.so`. First, this is not really correct, as `x_libraries` would be added to a search path. Second, this apparently does not work for sysroots created by crosstool-ng for some reason, likely because it wants to find other libraries in the same location.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We should just drop the `libX11.so` parts, and leave only the path.</description>
